==English==

===Etymology===
From Neo-Latin [[glagoliticus]] < Serbo-Croatian [[glagoljica]]/[[глагољица]] < [[Old Church Slavonic|OCS]] [[глагол|глаголъ]] ("word").

===Adjective===
'''Glagolitic'''
#Of or referring to the [[Glagolitic alphabet]].

===Proper noun===
'''Glagolitic'''
#The oldest known [[Slavonic]] alphabet, created by Saint [[Cyril]] around 862–863 AD. It was soon replaced by the [[Cyrillic]] alphabet.  The [[Croatian]] variant is still found in use in the Croatian Church along the [[Dalmatia]]n coast.  It was the first [[script]] (along with the Croatian language) that was granted special permission by the [[Vatican]] to be used in [[liturgy]] instead of [[Latin]].

